05/01/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis said the EU perspective of the Western Balkans and Turkey is the only way to guarantee the peace and stability of Southeast Europe. Describing Greece's foreign policy priorities for 2007 in a special Greek-language edition of The Economist, Bakoyannis said Greece is ready to actively contribute to the Euro-Atlantic integration of the region. She said Turkey is developing gradually into a modern European democracy, and added that efforts to boost bilateral relations and reduce tensions in the Aegean region have intensified. At the same time, she urged Turkey to meet its obligations to the EU regarding Cyprus. (Xinhua, Focus, Mediafax, Telma TV - 04/01/07)
